# Leviathan operator settings.
#
# Copy this to ~/.leviathan/env and fill in your values. leviathan-node.sh and
# install.sh source it, so you configure a dedicated RPC, wallet and run once
# instead of passing them on every command. Explicit env and flags still win.
#
#   mkdir -p ~/.leviathan && cp scripts/leviathan-env.example ~/.leviathan/env
#
# A dedicated devnet RPC is strongly recommended. The shared public endpoint
# (api.devnet.solana.com) rate-limits under a single node's transaction load,
# which stalls joins and ticks. Any provider with a devnet endpoint works.

# Dedicated RPC (replace with your provider endpoint):
# RPC=https://devnet.helius-rpc.com/?api-key=YOUR_KEY
# WS_RPC=wss://devnet.helius-rpc.com/?api-key=YOUR_KEY

# Which run to join (default leviathan-devnet):
# RUN_ID=leviathan-devnet

# Your funded devnet keypair:
# WALLET=/home/you/leviathan-node.json

# Optional bond to post before joining a bonded run:
# BOND=100

# Join confirmation deadline in seconds (raise on a slow RPC):
# LEVIATHAN_JOIN_TIMEOUT_SECS=45
